#### Marine Highway System

The [Alaska Marine Highway](/Alaska_Marine_Highway), alongside other Alaskan highways and routes, is recognized by the [Federal Highway Administration](/Federal_Highway_Administration) (FHWA) as eligible for federal funding. This aquatic artery was christened a [National Scenic Byway](/National_Scenic_Byway) by the FHWA on June 13, 2002, and subsequently elevated to the status of an [All-American Road](/All-American_Road) on September 22, 2005.

The system is segmented into distinct service regions: Southeast, Cross-Gulf, Prince William Sound, South-Central, and Southwest. [8] [9] [10]

